variable.name: PLATE_ID
variable.comment: Character field Non-blank = Field filled in. Blank = Field not filled in.

variable.value: Set to missing because CV was above allowable limit

variable.value: Set to missing because CV was above allowable limit

variable.name: IGF1R_I
variable.description: Indicator variable for Insulin-like growth factor 1 receptor
variable.value: Set to missing because CV was above allowable limit

variable.name: MMP8_I
variable.value: Set to missing because CV was above allowable limit

variable.name: IDTYPE
variable.comment: IDTYPE and ID taken together form a unique study participant identification number.

variable.name: ANAX1
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for ANAX1 is 9.76E+02 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 7.25E+04 pg/mL. ANAX1 values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use ANAX1_I to see what records are below and above these limits.

variable.name: GZMB
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for GZMB is 5.78E+00 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 4.54E+03 pg/mL. GZMB values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use GZMB_I to see what records are below and above these limits.

variable.name: IGF1R
variable.description: Insulin-like growth factor 1 receptor (sample type: plasma)
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for IGF1R is 7.86E+02 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 5.73E+05 pg/mL. IGF1R values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use IGF1R_I to see what records are below and above these limits. IGF1R values were set to unknown if IGF1R_CV was greater than or equal to 137.0 for Offspring (IDTYPE= 1) or 116.0 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3)

variable.name: IGF1R_CV
variable.description: CV for Insulin-like growth factor 1 receptor
variable.comment: IGF1R values were set to unknown if IGF1R_CV was greater than or equal to 137.0 for Offspring (IDTYPE= 1) or 116.0 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3)

variable.name: MMP8
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for MMP8 is 6.76E+01pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 5.37E+04 pg/mL. MMP8 values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use MMP8_I to see what records are below and above these limits. MMP8 values were set to unknown if MMP8_CV was greater than or equal to 76.9 for Offspring (IDTYPE= 1) or 98.9 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3)

variable.name: MMP8_CV
variable.comment: MMP8 values were set to unknown if MMP8_CV was greater than or equal to 76.9 for Offspring (IDTYPE= 1) or 98.9 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3)

variable.name: RUN_DATE
variable.comment: Date includes month, day and year, however, coding manual displays only month and year to preserve confidentiality.
